On the way this morning to Wokingham for a customer meeting. The 7:16am train from Redhill to Reading was running late and - in order to not affect their on-time stats, gWr decided to remove the stops between Guildford to Reading and kicked out the customers not travelling straight to Reading out onto Guildford!!!! 
Customer experience: a blatant 0
@GWR: how do you think customers appreciate being expandable and being asked to leave the train that was supposed to bring them to their destination????
